properties.areaDesc: Central U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca; East Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca; West Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 15 at 9:01PM PST until January 16 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Storm Warning, east winds 40 to 50 kt seas 7 to 9
feet. For the Gale Warning, east to southeast winds 30 to 40 kt
and seas 4 to 7 feet. At the west Entrance, combined seas 10 to
12 feet at 10 seconds building to 16 or 17 feet at 12 seconds.

* WHERE...West Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca,
Central U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca and East Entrance
U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...For the Storm Warning, until 10 PM PST this evening.
For the Gale Warning, from 10 PM this evening to 4 AM PST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Very strong winds will cause hazardous seas which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should remain in port, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST THURSDAY
